Building and running the octopos has dependencies on the following packages:

- autoconf-archive
- libcmocka0
- libcmocka-dev
- procps
- iproute2
- build-essential
- git
- pkg-config
- gcc
- libtool
- automake
- libssl-dev
- uthash-dev
- autoconf
- doxygen
- libjson-c-dev
- libini-config-dev
- libcurl4-openssl-dev
- libgcrypt-dev
- libglib2.0-dev

On Ubuntu use the following command:

sudo apt -y install autoconf-archive libcmocka0 libcmocka-dev procps \
  iproute2 build-essential git pkg-config gcc libtool automake libssl-dev \
  uthash-dev autoconf doxygen libjson-c-dev libini-config-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev \
  libgcrypt-dev libglib2.0-dev

Use the following sequence to build and install the octopos:

make umode

To build and run octops with a simulated TPM do:

make

To create a TPM environment do:

./external/ibmtpm1637/tpm_server
sudo -u tss tpm2-abrmd --tcti=mssim
